Date: Sun 16 Nov 2003
From: "BERGER" <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: The Gideon Database, Sun 16 Nov 2003 [edited]



China (Hong Kong S.A.R.): Hand, Foot and Mouth Disease
------------------------------------------------------
[The following information has been extracted from the Gideon Database by
Steve Berger]

477 patients were hospitalized for hand foot and mouth disease [HFM] in
1999. Enterovirus 71 was identified in 22, of which 3 developed
neurological complications and 1 died.

111 patients were hospitalized for HFM in 2000. Enterovirus 71 was
identified in 6 - 1 fatal.

114 patients were hospitalized for HFM in 2001 (none with complications).

192 patients were hospitalized for HFM in 2002 (one with complications).

--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
